6agf A 1024 B 181

A redox-regulated disulphide may form between Sodium channel protein type 4 subunit alpha and Sodium channel subunit beta-1 at these cysteines. However, the redox score of this cysteine pair is lower than any known redox-active disulphide.

Peptide name
Sodium channel protein type 4 subunit alpha

6agf A 729 A 731

A redox-regulated disulphide may form within Sodium channel protein type 4 subunit alpha at these cysteines. However, the redox score of this cysteine pair is lower than any known redox-active disulphide.

Peptide name
Sodium channel protein type 4 subunit alpha

6agf A 1576 A 1579

A redox-regulated disulphide may form within Sodium channel protein type 4 subunit alpha at these cysteines. However, the redox score of this cysteine pair is lower than any known redox-active disulphide.
